Phase 1 Features 
1. Places Near Me (Listing & Search)
Input: User’s location (GPS / manual search).
Output: List of monasteries near user.
Later Enhancement: Map-based display (Google Maps API / Mapbox).
2. Place Details Page
Input: User clicks a monastery.
Output: Show monastery details (history, description, images, rating).
Extra: Link to guides & AR/VR assets.
3. Open 3D View Page
Input: User clicks “View in 3D”.
Output: Render monastery’s 3D model (GLB/FBX/OBJ).
Tech: WebGL/Three.js or Babylon.js for browser rendering.
4. AR Interaction Mode
Input: User opens AR camera (mobile).
Output:
Video feed + 3D overlay (monk/guide bot).
AI bot speaks monastery info from knowledge base.
AI bot answers user questions (Q&A chatbot with contextual data).



UI pages : 
1. Home page -> Current location + nearby places categorised views 
2. Monastry details page (has the buttons for interact with ar bot and get in 3d view and a basic chatbot that gives basic details)



stack : 
Next.js 14 (App Router)
Prisma ORM for Postgres
TailwindCSS for styling
Three.js for 3D rendering
API Routes for backend endpoints
